00:23:13,225 --> 00:23:15,685
For 300,000 won? How much will you need?

267
00:23:15,685 --> 00:23:17,396
Why the rush?

268
00:23:17,979 --> 00:23:20,690
I'll do it for 450,000. I'm busy.

269
00:23:20,690 --> 00:23:23,193
He's taking me to Jeju next week.

270
00:23:23,193 --> 00:23:25,654
I have to decide if I want to sleep with him.

271
00:23:27,155 --> 00:23:30,325
Of course! Be careful not to crash.

272
00:23:31,743 --> 00:23:34,496
I have to watch out. I almost said "whore".

273
00:23:35,330 --> 00:23:38,166
Jesus. I don't even want to insult you.

274
00:23:38,834 --> 00:23:42,254
Do you know what the only place is
which has class grades?

275
00:23:42,921 --> 00:23:44,172
Aircraft.

276
00:23:44,172 --> 00:23:47,175
First class, business and economic.

277
00:23:47,175 --> 00:23:50,637
Only a curtain separates them,
but no one is allowed to cross it.

278
00:23:51,221 --> 00:23:52,431
What are you blabbing about?

279
00:23:52,931 --> 00:23:54,933
I'm telling you to stay behind the curtain

280
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:58,145
because you earn barely enough
to feed yourself.

281
00:23:58,770 --> 00:24:00,188
I will cross the curtain.

282
00:24:01,940 --> 00:24:03,859
Stop Jae-jun's car.

283
00:24:44,065 --> 00:24:45,233
That's interesting?

284
00:24:46,193 --> 00:24:49,905
The game was already decided,
but she decided to stretch it.

285
00:24:49,905 --> 00:24:51,114
Why?

286
00:24:51,114 --> 00:24:52,616
Who?

287
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,159
In the go club.

288
00:24:56,411 --> 00:24:57,245
What was it?

289
00:24:58,413 --> 00:25:00,707
I'm going to sleep and then I'm going to work.

290
00:25:02,501 --> 00:25:04,711
It gives me a headache. Not you?

291
00:25:05,212 --> 00:25:07,881
It is neat, fun and pleasing to the eye.

292
00:25:07,881 --> 00:25:10,050
Why do you smoke? That's not healthy.

293
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:11,051
You're right.

294
00:25:11,885 --> 00:25:16,014
Why did you marry a smoker when you don't smoke?

295
00:25:16,014 --> 00:25:18,266
You're neat, if we ignore the smoking.

296
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:21,728
You are fun and pleasing to the eye.

297
00:25:23,688 --> 00:25:25,440
And that's why I like you!

298
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:27,692
You have the answer to everything.

299
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:33,114
But you went on three blind dates,
including the one with me.

300
00:25:33,615 --> 00:25:34,699
Why did you take me?

301
00:25:34,699 --> 00:25:36,952
You wore the least amount of clothes.

302
00:25:37,494 --> 00:25:40,747
You wore the least amount of clothes,
but clothes from Dior.

303
00:25:42,457 --> 00:25:44,042
How crazy you are!

304
00:25:44,876 --> 00:25:48,129
You are gentle, but sometimes you can be cruel.

305
00:25:50,382 --> 00:25:52,050
If you're coming, hurry up.

306
00:25:52,592 --> 00:25:55,845
I will wear very few clothes to bed.

307
00:25:56,638 --> 00:25:57,472
In five minutes.

308
00:26:48,982 --> 00:26:49,899
Am I dreaming?

309
00:26:51,943 --> 00:26:53,153
Are you talking to me?

310
00:26:54,696 --> 00:26:55,614
I sorted myself out.

311
00:27:03,580 --> 00:27:04,581
<i>Give me 10 min.</i>

312
00:27:08,877 --> 00:27:10,962
Did you pass the teacher's exam?

313
00:27:12,047 --> 00:27:14,382
- I did.
- Did you?

314
00:27:15,592 --> 00:27:16,676
Congratulations.

315
00:27:17,719 --> 00:27:19,679
Maybe I'm late.

316
00:27:20,722 --> 00:27:21,723
Thanks.

317
00:27:28,855 --> 00:27:32,108
I am going to Semyeong for an academic conference.

318
00:27:36,780 --> 00:27:37,614
are you ok

319
00:27:39,074 --> 00:27:39,908
I am.

320
00:27:40,992 --> 00:27:43,328
I heard you were a medic in the army.

321
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:45,914
I got out of the army a long time ago.

322
00:27:47,082 --> 00:27:48,667
Where did you hear that?

323
00:27:49,542 --> 00:27:51,378
From the old men in the park.

324
00:27:52,253 --> 00:27:56,257
A young unemployed man joined the army
and came back a new man.

325
00:28:00,929 --> 00:28:02,263
Were you in the park?

326
00:28:05,850 --> 00:28:08,103
Should I have written you a letter?

327
00:28:08,103 --> 00:28:10,355
Are paramedics allowed to receive letters?

328
00:28:11,147 --> 00:28:14,150
- We get love.
- Did you get a lot of them?

329
00:28:20,323 --> 00:28:21,449
FOR JOO YEO-JEONG

330
00:28:21,449 --> 00:28:23,451
FROM CHEONGSONG PRISON

331
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:25,161
I don't like letters.

332
00:28:27,372 --> 00:28:29,290
What brings you to Semyeong?

333
00:28:30,041 --> 00:28:31,126
Do you work there?

334
00:28:31,876 --> 00:28:32,711
Not yet.

335
00:28:33,294 --> 00:28:35,463
I went there on business.

336
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:38,883
Is he with you?

337
00:28:39,676 --> 00:28:41,344
He's been staring for a while.

338
00:28:43,596 --> 00:28:45,181
I have to go.

339
00:28:49,060 --> 00:28:49,894
Me too.

340
00:28:50,812 --> 00:28:52,021
Just so you know...

341
00:28:54,023 --> 00:28:54,899
then,

342
00:28:55,817 --> 00:28:58,194
when we started playing go in the park,

343
00:28:59,320 --> 00:29:03,575
it was the coldest period of my life.

344
00:29:06,244 --> 00:29:08,288
But the hours with you...

345
00:29:10,665 --> 00:29:14,169
they were my only constant
and the only companionship.

346
00:29:16,087 --> 00:29:18,173
If I seemed warm,

347
00:29:19,549 --> 00:29:21,134
you are responsible for that.

348
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:26,181
It was eating me up.

349
00:29:36,941 --> 00:29:38,109
I work here.

350
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:40,862
If you are interested.

351
00:29:44,657 --> 00:29:45,784
Have a good trip.

352
00:29:56,544 --> 00:30:01,132
SEOUL JOO GENERAL HOSPITAL
JOO YEO-JEONG, PLASTIC SURGEON

353
00:30:12,143 --> 00:30:13,228
Excuse me.

354
00:30:17,732 --> 00:30:19,818
Don't you live here?

355
00:30:19,818 --> 00:30:21,611
You are in apartment 301, right?

356
00:30:21,611 --> 00:30:24,197
I am the owner.

357
00:30:25,657 --> 00:30:26,574
Good evening.

358
00:30:27,116 --> 00:30:29,202
I'm asking if you live here.

359
00:30:29,202 --> 00:30:32,539
Your electricity and water bills
they are always low.

360
00:30:33,206 --> 00:30:34,874
I pay my rent on time.

361
00:30:34,874 --> 00:30:36,793
I know that.

362
00:30:36,793 --> 00:30:40,380
But you said you wanted an apartment so badly,

363
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:44,425
and now it has been empty for months.
I'm interested in what's going on.

364
00:30:46,010 --> 00:30:48,680
I haven't gotten a job in Semyeong yet.

365
00:30:49,264 --> 00:30:50,265
I'm trying.

366
00:30:55,770 --> 00:30:59,774
<i>I know we shouldn't meet,
but I have a recording.</i>

367
00:30:59,774 --> 00:31:01,150
<i>I will sit in the car.</i>

368
00:31:05,488 --> 00:31:07,365
You should have entered from the other side.

369
00:31:07,365 --> 00:31:10,577
Sorry, I'll write it down for another time.

370
00:31:12,453 --> 00:31:15,373
I enlarged the picture,
so the quality is not the best.

371
00:31:15,373 --> 00:31:17,166
You have to watch closely.

372
00:31:18,126 --> 00:31:18,960
Good.

373
00:31:30,179 --> 00:31:32,682
Here, look! Here!

374
00:31:43,401 --> 00:31:47,071
"Director,
why don't you sit in the front today?”

375
00:31:50,783 --> 00:31:51,784
I don't get it.

376
00:31:57,540 --> 00:32:00,877
"Love, you sit in the front today."

377
00:32:07,175 --> 00:32:09,010
The driver is Jo Soo-hyeon?

378
00:32:10,011 --> 00:32:11,179
How do you know?

379
00:32:11,846 --> 00:32:12,931
It wasn't a woman.

380
00:32:14,724 --> 00:32:17,435
He was on medication for erectile dysfunction.

381
00:32:17,435 --> 00:32:20,855
Gender does not play a role in this
as long as it can last.

382
00:32:22,065 --> 00:32:24,150
We should have focused on age.

383
00:32:27,612 --> 00:32:29,989
You are serious at odd times!

384
00:32:35,370 --> 00:32:36,746
What is it?

385
00:32:36,746 --> 00:32:40,249
You thought I couldn't laugh
because he always beats me?

386
00:32:41,125 --> 00:32:43,294
He may be beating me, but I'm happy.

387
00:32:43,294 --> 00:32:44,963
Lord!

388
00:32:50,176 --> 00:32:52,512
You should have told me that sooner.

389
00:32:53,346 --> 00:32:55,348
- What is that?
- That you are happy.

390
00:32:56,724 --> 00:32:58,351
I don't want to laugh.

391
00:32:59,394 --> 00:33:00,311
Why not?

392
00:33:03,481 --> 00:33:07,485
I'm afraid I will for laughs
forget what I should be doing.

393
00:33:11,406 --> 00:33:12,991
I didn't remember that.

394
00:33:14,409 --> 00:33:15,660
I'll be careful.

395
00:33:17,161 --> 00:33:18,371
Maybe that's why he's beating me.

396
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:20,289
Don't do that!

397
00:33:29,132 --> 00:33:31,801
I really like the way I am now.

398
00:33:32,802 --> 00:33:35,304
I'm happy, but I don't have a chance to be happy.

399
00:33:35,304 --> 00:33:37,974
Now that I've breathed, I always smile.

400
00:33:42,603 --> 00:33:45,523
Don't worry, I won't drag you down.

401
00:33:46,190 --> 00:33:47,859
Let's try now!

402
00:33:51,654 --> 00:33:54,323
<i>How come she and I... No.</i>

403
00:33:56,284 --> 00:33:58,369
<i>How come we have to try?</i>

404
00:33:59,537 --> 00:34:01,956
<i>Labor is extremely tiring.</i>

405
00:34:02,707 --> 00:34:05,209
<i>I'm tired of trying, Yeon-jin.</i>

406
00:34:05,209 --> 00:34:06,544
Here you go.

407
00:34:23,728 --> 00:34:25,563
How are you, Mr. Kim?

408
00:34:26,147 --> 00:34:27,565
It's me, Dong-eun.

409
00:34:29,108 --> 00:34:30,026
Who?

410
00:34:30,610 --> 00:34:31,944
Sunghan High School.

411
00:34:32,445 --> 00:34:35,073
I graduated in 2004.

412
00:34:35,573 --> 00:34:36,908
You don't remember me?

413
00:34:39,744 --> 00:34:41,245
What is your name?

414
00:34:48,127 --> 00:34:49,504
Soo-hane! Hi!

415
00:34:50,713 --> 00:34:52,465
Where did you come from?

416
00:34:52,465 --> 00:34:54,509
Dong-eun, what are you doing here?

417
00:34:55,093 --> 00:34:57,053
This is my house. This is my father.

418
00:34:57,053 --> 00:34:58,638
Seriously?

419
00:35:00,306 --> 00:35:01,974
How small the world is.

420
00:35:02,558 --> 00:35:04,352
I was your father's student.

421
00:35:07,980 --> 00:35:09,273
Do you remember me now?

422
00:35:10,358 --> 00:35:11,275
Well, of course.

423
00:35:11,275 --> 00:35:14,737
Mr. Kim, I'm a teacher now too.

424
00:35:19,659 --> 00:35:21,953
What did you say?

425
00:35:23,579 --> 00:35:24,413
about my son?

426
00:35:24,997 --> 00:35:27,125
Do it again! What did you say?

427
00:35:47,311 --> 00:35:50,481
Why are we here?
You should have come to Siesta.

428
00:35:52,608 --> 00:35:55,528
This building was abandoned
when we were at school.

429
00:35:56,237 --> 00:35:57,405
She is still like this.

430
00:35:57,989 --> 00:35:59,198
Enough chit chat.

431
00:36:00,616 --> 00:36:03,536
You want revenge, don't you?

432
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:04,954
That's right.

433
00:36:06,247 --> 00:36:07,957
Look at her. You're not scared.

434
00:36:08,666 --> 00:36:09,792
You left me out?

435
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:14,589
I can't take revenge on you. You have nothing.

436
00:36:15,173 --> 00:36:18,843
Others may lose something,
but you have nothing at all.

437
00:36:18,843 --> 00:36:21,304
Are you saying that to my face?

438
00:36:22,096 --> 00:36:24,223
I can push you out of here.

439
00:36:24,724 --> 00:36:25,683
Better watch out.

440
00:36:27,894 --> 00:36:28,728
I know.

441
00:36:29,937 --> 00:36:31,689
I stood here once.

442
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:33,858
Because you mistreated me.

443
00:36:34,358 --> 00:36:35,610
Are you threatening me?

444
00:36:37,987 --> 00:36:40,489
- At least you can be scared.
- You're asking for trouble.

445
00:36:45,870 --> 00:36:48,206
- Remember So-hee?
-What?

446
00:36:48,206 --> 00:36:52,126
It was said that she killed herself
when she went to a new school.

447
00:36:53,294 --> 00:36:54,712
You must remember her.

448
00:36:54,712 --> 00:36:57,798
Before you said, “Here comes Dong-eun,”

449
00:36:58,758 --> 00:37:01,010
you must have been saying, "Here comes So-hee."

450
00:37:07,975 --> 00:37:10,061
This is where So-hee fell.

451
00:37:11,020 --> 00:37:12,313
But she didn't kill herself.

452
00:37:22,823 --> 00:37:25,826
What the hell? I didn't do it!

453
00:37:25,826 --> 00:37:27,078
I didn't kill her!

454
00:37:27,078 --> 00:37:28,162
I know.

455
00:37:29,372 --> 00:37:31,958
Take the money from the person who killed her.

456
00:37:32,625 --> 00:37:34,126
That's my information.

457
00:37:39,966 --> 00:37:41,050
Who did it?

458
00:37:42,468 --> 00:37:45,137
I told you. My work is a priority.

459
00:37:51,352 --> 00:37:54,689
They were not easy to find.
Everything is full of dog hair.

460
00:37:55,523 --> 00:37:57,358
Ten to the root, right?

461
00:37:57,358 --> 00:37:58,276
Wait.

462
00:37:59,318 --> 00:38:00,152
Are you...

463
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:03,864
You gave birth to Jae-jun's child?

464
00:38:05,366 --> 00:38:06,784
Only if you are too.

465
00:38:08,202 --> 00:38:09,912
I'll call you when I confirm.

466
00:38:15,626 --> 00:38:17,253
<i>I didn't leave you out.</i>

467
00:38:18,212 --> 00:38:19,964
<i>You can lose something too.</i>

468
00:38:20,464 --> 00:38:21,590
<i>Just one.</i>

469
00:38:22,466 --> 00:38:23,467
<i>My life.</i>

470
00:39:00,004 --> 00:39:02,757
In hand! She says the back of her hand hurts.

471
00:39:02,757 --> 00:39:07,094
Sa-ra, wake up!
You have to clean up and go to the exhibition.

472
00:39:07,094 --> 00:39:09,347
It's too bright.

473
00:39:10,931 --> 00:39:12,099
Are you an angel?

474
00:39:12,099 --> 00:39:14,435
Come on, get up.

475
00:39:14,935 --> 00:39:17,104
You have a special exhibition today.

476
00:39:18,439 --> 00:39:21,275
If you really have to smoke something,
take something weaker.

477
00:39:21,275 --> 00:39:23,152
There are also thinner cigarettes.

478
00:39:23,152 --> 00:39:25,029
Is there such a thing for drugs?

479
00:39:26,489 --> 00:39:32,370
LEE SA-RE SPECIAL EXHIBITION
OBSERVATION OF THE IDEAL IN A SLEEP

480
00:39:35,956 --> 00:39:37,625
I want one.

481
00:39:38,876 --> 00:39:40,211
Send her to the club.

482
00:39:40,211 --> 00:39:42,755
You have to pay for shipping, dear customer.

483
00:39:42,755 --> 00:39:44,006
The rich are greedy.

484
00:39:44,006 --> 00:39:46,675
It will all come back to me after taxes.

485
00:39:46,675 --> 00:39:48,469
I'm actually doing a good deed.

486
00:39:48,469 --> 00:39:50,638
That's how it goes with income tax.

487
00:39:50,638 --> 00:39:54,016
You wouldn't know that
because you don't earn enough.

488
00:39:58,020 --> 00:39:58,938
Sa-ra?

489
00:39:59,730 --> 00:40:01,232
Hide the drink.

490
00:40:04,527 --> 00:40:07,905
- Wife of Director Jang from Buil.
- I'm glad!

491
00:40:08,447 --> 00:40:10,699
The pictures are beautiful.

492
00:40:10,699 --> 00:40:15,121
How God gifted the artist Lee
such a lavish gift?

493
00:40:15,704 --> 00:40:16,622
Amen.

494
00:40:17,832 --> 00:40:19,417
She bought three paintings.

495
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:21,085
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

496
00:40:21,585 --> 00:40:22,461
- This way.
- Good.

497
00:40:22,461 --> 00:40:24,130
We need your address.

498
00:40:24,130 --> 00:40:26,173
Shall we send them to your home?

499
00:40:27,174 --> 00:40:30,469
Why are you so normal, artist Lee?

500
00:40:31,679 --> 00:40:34,265
Next month I will receive an award.

501
00:40:34,849 --> 00:40:37,184
Will you come so I don't embarrass myself?

502
00:40:37,810 --> 00:40:39,061
And you, artist Lee.

503
00:40:39,061 --> 00:40:41,313
Fuck it, stop it.

504
00:40:42,690 --> 00:40:45,025
What prize will you get?

505
00:40:45,985 --> 00:40:47,486
CEREMONY FOR GRADUATES

506
00:40:51,115 --> 00:40:55,619
It hasn't changed at all.
I haven't been here since graduation.

507
00:40:55,619 --> 00:40:58,372
Seriously? You haven't seen the physical education teacher?

508
00:40:58,372 --> 00:41:01,542
Hye-jeong left him. He was crying.

509
00:41:01,542 --> 00:41:03,294
- You haven't been to Korea?
- I didn't.

510
00:41:03,294 --> 00:41:08,757
In Paris, I watched <i>Lovers in Paris.</i>
It took me three days to download the episode.

511
00:41:08,757 --> 00:41:10,092
So much fun.

512
00:41:10,634 --> 00:41:12,553
Why isn't the jerk answering?

513
00:41:13,053 --> 00:41:14,305
I need something.

514
00:41:14,305 --> 00:41:15,347
Myeong-oh?

515
00:41:16,223 --> 00:41:17,808
He still doesn't answer today?

516
00:41:17,808 --> 00:41:20,978
I need something too! Do you know anything about it?

517
00:41:20,978 --> 00:41:23,230
He's probably drunk and asleep.

518
00:41:24,607 --> 00:41:26,317
I have to fire that monkey.

519
00:41:55,054 --> 00:41:57,640
Long time no see.

520
00:41:58,349 --> 00:42:00,017
are you ok

521
00:42:00,935 --> 00:42:02,686
I've seen her somewhere before.

522
00:42:03,479 --> 00:42:07,983
17 years have passed
since when were all six of us together?

523
00:42:08,567 --> 00:42:11,070
Five. Myeong-o is not here.

524
00:42:11,070 --> 00:42:12,947
I know! Moon So-hee, right?

525
00:42:13,864 --> 00:42:16,867
You always mix up names.
Moon Dong-eun and Yoon So-hee.

526
00:42:16,867 --> 00:42:20,746
I heard that she worked in a factory.

527
00:42:20,746 --> 00:42:22,248
What are you doing here?

528
00:42:22,248 --> 00:42:24,500
You didn't graduate.

529
00:42:24,500 --> 00:42:27,461
Sorry, my fond memories are hazy.

530
00:42:27,461 --> 00:42:29,713
Good to see you, So-hee.

531
00:42:29,713 --> 00:42:30,631
Dong-eun.

532
00:42:32,967 --> 00:42:35,511
I come to this hall every so often.

533
00:42:36,470 --> 00:42:40,307
But today, all the friendly faces are here.

534
00:42:41,684 --> 00:42:43,102
How are you, Yeon-jin?

535
00:42:43,602 --> 00:42:45,437
I love your forecasts.

536
00:42:46,647 --> 00:42:50,651
On TV, you seem like a really good person.

537
00:42:55,489 --> 00:42:56,323
And you?

538
00:42:59,994 --> 00:43:01,579
how are you

539
00:43:01,579 --> 00:43:05,082
I got a new job, so I'm working a lot.

540
00:43:06,667 --> 00:43:09,670
I bought new clothes
and ate expensive <i>sashimi.</i>

541
00:43:09,670 --> 00:43:13,090
You are the chief director of schools in Semyeong?

542
00:43:13,090 --> 00:43:14,466
Congratulations.

543
00:43:19,096 --> 00:43:20,931
Who are you?

544
00:43:20,931 --> 00:43:23,100
Did you dig through my trash?

545
00:43:23,100 --> 00:43:24,810
I had no choice.

546
00:43:25,686 --> 00:43:28,355
Is your driver Jo Soo-hyeon?

547
00:43:29,607 --> 00:43:32,526
Do your son and future daughter-in-law know

548
00:43:33,360 --> 00:43:37,615
that they will share the inheritance
with Jo Soo-hyeon?

549
00:43:38,449 --> 00:43:41,702
Are you threatening me?

550
00:43:43,245 --> 00:43:44,163
Sorry.

551
00:43:44,663 --> 00:43:47,333
What I am looking for is very simple.

552
00:43:47,333 --> 00:43:50,919
I want to be a 1-2 class teacher
at Semyeong Elementary School.

553
00:43:51,920 --> 00:43:53,505
I am qualified.

554
00:43:54,089 --> 00:43:55,841
I live in Semyeong.

555
00:43:55,841 --> 00:43:58,761
I quit my job at my current school.

556
00:43:59,845 --> 00:44:00,846
Are you a teacher?

557
00:44:01,430 --> 00:44:02,264
I am.

558
00:44:03,474 --> 00:44:07,061
May I start working?
when does the new semester start?

559
00:44:07,770 --> 00:44:09,855
SEMYEONG PRIMARY SCHOOL

560
00:44:25,204 --> 00:44:28,582
HA YE-SOL

561
00:44:32,086 --> 00:44:34,588
<i>We will start awarding prizes immediately.</i>

562
00:44:34,588 --> 00:44:39,009
<i>This is an award for Park Yeon-jin,
23rd class graduate.</i>

563
00:44:42,096 --> 00:44:44,390
CEREMONY FOR GRADUATES

564
00:44:49,269 --> 00:44:52,523
<i>From now on, your days will be a nightmare.</i>

565
00:44:53,357 --> 00:44:55,609
<i>It will be provocative and frightening.</i>

566
00:44:56,443 --> 00:44:59,405
<i>You can't stop me or remove me.</i>

567
00:45:00,948 --> 00:45:06,745
<i>I intend to become
your very old rumor, Yeon-jin.</i>

568
00:45:20,092 --> 00:45:21,260
That, Yeon-jin!

569
00:45:22,720 --> 00:45:24,054
Bravo!

570
00:45:25,013 --> 00:45:26,932
You're fantastic, Yeon-jin!

571
00:47:48,365 --> 00:47:53,365
End of episode 3


